From git@z Thu Jan  1 00:00:00 1970
Subject: [PATCH 8/8] RDMA/bnxt_re: Fix UBSAN shift in alloc_init_hwq for zero depth/stride
From: Stephen Bates <sbates@raithlin.com>
Date: Tue, 01 Apr 2026 12:00:00 -0600
Message-Id: <20260401-bnxt-fix-ubsan-hwq-v1@raithlin.com>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="utf-8"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

After the QP creation refactor (patch 0002), bnxt_re_setup_qp_hwqs()
calls bnxt_qplib_alloc_init_hwq() for both SQ and RQ unconditionally.
When the DV path creates a QP without an RQ (qprva==0), it zeroes
rq.max_wqe so get_depth() returns 0.  The standard verbs path can
also produce zero depth for certain QP configurations.

roundup_pow_of_two(0) triggers undefined behavior: fls_long(0 - 1)
returns 64, producing a 1UL << 64 shift. UBSAN reports:

  shift-out-of-bounds in include/linux/log2.h:57:13
  shift exponent 64 is too large for 64-bit type 'long unsigned int'

Fix by:
1. Returning 0 (success with empty HWQ) from
   bnxt_qplib_alloc_init_hwq() when both depth and
   aux_depth are zero.  The HWQ level is set to
   PBL_LVL_0 so downstream FW command assembly sees
   a valid (empty) queue descriptor.
2. Guarding roundup_pow_of_two() calls for stride
   and aux_stride which could also be zero.
3. Defaulting pgsize to PAGE_SIZE when the caller
   leaves it uninitialized (zero), preventing
   division-by-zero in the npages calculation.

Signed-off-by: Stephen Bates <sbates@raithlin.com>
---
 drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_res.c | 14 +++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_res.c b/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_res.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_res.c
+++ b/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_res.c
@@ -196,11 +196,23 @@ int bnxt_qplib_alloc_init_hwq(struct bnxt_qplib_hwq *hwq,
 	pdev = res->pdev;
 	pg_size = hwq_attr->sginfo->pgsize;
 	hwq->level = PBL_LVL_MAX;
 
-	depth = roundup_pow_of_two(hwq_attr->depth);
-	stride = roundup_pow_of_two(hwq_attr->stride);
+	if (!hwq_attr->depth && !hwq_attr->aux_depth) {
+		hwq->level = PBL_LVL_0;
+		return 0;
+	}
+
+	if (!pg_size)
+		pg_size = PAGE_SIZE;
+
+	depth = hwq_attr->depth ?
+		roundup_pow_of_two(hwq_attr->depth) : 0;
+	stride = hwq_attr->stride ?
+		roundup_pow_of_two(hwq_attr->stride) : 0;
 	if (hwq_attr->aux_depth) {
 		aux_slots = hwq_attr->aux_depth;
-		aux_size = roundup_pow_of_two(hwq_attr->aux_stride);
+		aux_size = hwq_attr->aux_stride ?
+			roundup_pow_of_two(hwq_attr->aux_stride) : 0;
 		aux_pages = (aux_slots * aux_size) / pg_size;
 		if ((aux_slots * aux_size) % pg_size)
 			aux_pages++;
